    "untyped_fraction": 0.0049,
    "insight": "OEIS is overwhelmingly integer: 93.3% of sequences are pure integers (nonn+sign). Only 2.0% are rationals (frac) and 4.2% represent reals (cons+cofr). This is by design: OEIS was founded as an integer sequence encyclopedia. Non-integer sequences were added later and are structurally distinct \u2014 they have higher 'more'/'hard' rates (harder to extend), lower finite rates, and different naming patterns (decimal expansions, numerators/denominators)."
